# ============================================================
# HFLootFilter.conf — Loot crate building allowlist
# File: $profile:HFLootFilter.conf (copy this .example, drop the suffix)
#
# Controls which buildings receive loot crates. Applied during the
# town scan in HFSpawnUtils.FindBuildingInteriorPositions.
#
# Format: one rule per line.
#   ALLOW <path-substring>
#   DENY  <path-substring>
# Comments: # or //
#
# RESOLUTION (firewall-style, FIRST-MATCH-WINS):
#   1. Walk rules top-to-bottom.
#   2. First rule whose <path-substring> is contained in the prefab
#      path decides the result.
#   3. If NO rule matches, the path is REJECTED (default-deny, safer
#      for custom-map content).
#
# Admin convention: put SPECIFIC rules first, BROAD rules last.
# Examples:
#   DENY /Industrial/Cranes/    # block cranes
#   ALLOW /Industrial/          # allow all other industrial
# A prefab path containing both patterns hits DENY first → rejected.
#
# If this file is missing entirely, the server falls back to its
# hardcoded defaults (identical to the rules below) so loot still
# spawns. Edit this file to customise; remove it to restore defaults.
# ============================================================

# --- DENY non-building categories (debris, destruction variants, etc.) ---
DENY /BuildingParts/
DENY /Debris/
DENY /Signs/
DENY /Walls/
DENY /Dst/

# --- Specific ALLOWs inside Infrastructure ---
# Infrastructure as a category is mostly poles, railings, lamps —
# not lootable. But a few sub-trees contain real buildings with
# doors and ladders. These must appear BEFORE any broader Infrastructure
# deny rule an admin might add later.
ALLOW /Infrastructure/Naval/Lighthouse/
ALLOW /Infrastructure/Waterworks/
ALLOW /Infrastructure/Power/

# --- Broad ALLOW categories (actual buildings) ---
ALLOW /Houses/
ALLOW /Commercial/
ALLOW /Services/
ALLOW /Cultural/
ALLOW /Ruins/

# Agriculture — specific sub-dirs only (skip Gates, Hopper, Manure, etc.)
# Note: "Barn" singular — the directory is not "Barns".
ALLOW /Agriculture/Barn
ALLOW /Agriculture/CowShed/
ALLOW /Agriculture/Hayloft/
ALLOW /Agriculture/Greenhouse/

# Industrial — specific sub-dirs (skip Cableways, Cranes, Pipelines, etc.)
ALLOW /Industrial/Houses/
ALLOW /Industrial/Garages/
ALLOW /Industrial/Silos/

# Military — houses, barracks, depots, bunkers, training facilities.
# Military/Airport is covered by the /Airport/ rule below.
ALLOW /Military/Houses/
ALLOW /Military/Barracks
ALLOW /Military/Depots/
ALLOW /Military/Bunkers/
ALLOW /Military/Training/
ALLOW /Military/Fortifications/

# Airport — ControlTower, Hangar (top-level Airport/ AND Military/Airport/)
ALLOW /Airport/

# Recreation — cottage, gym, rec center, beach structures
ALLOW /Recreation/

# Forest — hunter deer stands (climbable platforms via ladder)
ALLOW /Forest/DeerStands/

# ============================================================
# Everything else is REJECTED by default (no rule matches).
# Add more ALLOW rules above to accept custom prefabs from your
# map. Add DENY rules at the TOP to block specific prefabs even
# if a broader ALLOW rule below would accept them.
# ============================================================
